                     <interp inst="t18450818-1790-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450818-1790-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing 1 rule, value 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18450818-name-1122" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1122" type="surname" value="PEGRUM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1122" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450818-1790-offence-1 t18450818-name-1122"></join>John Pegrum</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1123" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1123" type="surname" value="PEGRUM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1123" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PEGRUM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter, and live in Robert-atreet, Brixton—the prisoner worked in my service. I missed a rule, which I had laid on the stone pavement where we were at work—I spoke to the prisoner about it—he said he did not believe I had had a rule there that morning—this it my rule.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you hear of it from Randall? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I expect I had laid the rule on the pavement—the prisoner came about nine or ten o'clock, and I missed the rule about one.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1124" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1124" type="surname" value="RANDALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1124" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM RANDALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner have the rule between eleven and twelve o'clock that morning—he said he had found it in the drain—he afterwards said he had sold it for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. and told me not to say anything about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> He showed it you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I saw it was my master's—I told him so, and read the name on it—he then said, "Don't say anything about it."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1125" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1125" type="surname" value="PERKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1125" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PERKINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I bought the rule for 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you rub it with sand-paper, to erase the name? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I do not know the name—I cannot read.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1126" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1126" type="surname" value="PEGRUM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1126" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PEGRUM</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> This rule had my name on it—it is partly erased, but you can see it now.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1127" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1127" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1127" type="surname" value="WEBB"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1127" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD WEBB</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 228.) I took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> In going to the station, did he not say he knew where the rule was, he would get it back, and you need not take him up? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he said he found it down the drain, and he thought all he found he could do as he liked with.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
